title: Plastics and Rubber Machinery (Euromap)
description: OPC 40083 (Euromap83): General information regarding plastics and rubber machines. The intention is that ObjectTypes which can be used for several machines and applications are defined only once. For specific applications (e.g. connection of injection molding machines to MES), it is extended by specific Companion Specifications (e.g. EUROMAP 77).

    <UADataType NodeId="ns=1;i=3020" BrowseName="1:CavityCycleQualityEnumeration">
        <DisplayName>CavityCycleQualityEnumeration</DisplayName>
        <Description>Quality of the cycle for each cavity</Description>
        <References>
            <Reference ReferenceType="HasSubtype" IsForward="false">i=29</Reference>
            <Reference ReferenceType="HasProperty">ns=1;i=6216</Reference>
        </References>

            <Field Name="NO_PART" Value="0">
                <Description>There is no part in cavity</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="GOOD_PART" Value="1">
                <Description>The machine has detected no failures during the cycle for this cavity and the part quality is assumed as good</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="BAD_PART" Value="2">
                <Description>The machine has detected failures during the cycle for the cavity and the part quality is assumed as bad</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="REWORK" Value="3">
                <Description>The machine has detected failures during the cycle for the cavity which might be fixed by reworking the part</Description>
            </Field>
        </Definition>
    </UADataType>

    <UADataType NodeId="ns=1;i=3017" BrowseName="1:JobStatusEnumeration">
        <DisplayName>JobStatusEnumeration</DisplayName>
        <Description>Current status of the job</Description>
        <References>
            <Reference ReferenceType="HasProperty">ns=1;i=6264</Reference>
            <Reference ReferenceType="HasSubtype" IsForward="false">i=29</Reference>
        </References>
        <Definition Name="1:JobStatusEnumeration">
            <Field Name="OTHER" Value="0">
                <Description>This state is used if none of the other states below apply</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="TRANSFERRED_ASSIGNED" Value="1">
                <Description>The job has been transferred to the machine and assigned as current job</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="SET_UP_ACTIVE" Value="2">
                <Description>The operator prepares the machine for the job</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="SET_UP_INTERRUPTED" Value="3">
                <Description>The operator has interrupted but not finished the preparation of the machine for the job</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="SET_UP_FINISHED" Value="4">
                <Description>The operator has finished the preparation of the machine for the job</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="START_UP_ACTIVE" Value="5">
                <Description>The operator is setting the machine in the start-up phase</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="JOB_IN_PRODUCTION" Value="6">
                <Description>The machine is producing parts/products for the job</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="JOB_INTERRUPTED" Value="7">
                <Description>The job is interrupted. The nominal output is not reached</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="JOB_FINISHED" Value="8">
                <Description>Nominal output reached</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="TEAR_DOWN_ACTIVE" Value="9">
                <Description>The operator tears the machine down</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="TEAR_DOWN_INTERRUPTED" Value="10">
                <Description>Tear-down is interrupted but not finished</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="TEAR_DOWN_FINISHED" Value="11">
                <Description>Tear-down is finished</Description>
            </Field>
        </Definition>
    </UADataType>

                <Description>This state is used if none of the other states below apply</Description>

            <Field Name="NO_PRODUCTION" Value="1">
                <Description>The machine does not produce any parts/products</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="START_UP" Value="2">
                <Description>The machine is producing parts/products in the start-up phase. So the correct settings of the machines are not reached.</Description>

            <Field Name="READY_FOR_PRODUCTION" Value="3">
                <Description>The machine is producing parts/products, the correct settings of the machines are reached but the production is not yet released (e.g. waiting for release from quality assurance)</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="PRODUCTION" Value="4">
                <Description>The machine is producing parts/products.
In semi-automatic mode also during waiting time (e.g. for manual loading/unloading of parts) ProductionStatus remains in this state (time out possible if e.g. cycle time exceeds a pre-defined limit)</Description>
            </Field>
            <Field Name="DRY_RUN" Value="5">
                <Description>The machine is moving without material</Description>
            </Field>
        </Definition>
    </UADataType>
